			<common:generalComment xml:lang="en">Ferric chloride is a common compound of iron and chlorine in which iron possesses +3 oxidation state. It is a deliquescent dark salt FeCl3 that readily hydrates to the yellow-orange form and is used especially for etching, in sewage treatment, and as an astringent. In its anhydrous form, FeCl3, it occurs as a black-brown, water-soluble solid; in its hydrated form, FeCl3⋅xH2O, it occurs in orange-yellow, deliquescent crystals.</common:generalComment>
			<common:generalComment xml:lang="zh">氯化铁是铁和氯的常见化合物，其中铁的氧化态为 +3。它是一种易潮解的深色盐 FeCl3，很容易水合成为橘黄色，特别用于蚀刻、污水处理和收敛剂。它的无水形态是 FeCl3，呈黑褐色水溶性固体；水合形态是 FeCl3⋅xH2O，呈橙黄色潮解晶体。</common:generalComment>
